","created_at":"2026-04-20T06:05:54.000-05:00","title":"Your engineering team looks healthy. It probably isn't","url":"https://dbarabashh.com/thoughts-and-experience/your-engineering-team-looks-healthy","score":6,"flags":1,"comment_count":3,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"brbash","user_is_author":true,"tags":["culture","practices","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cjbxjv","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cjbxjv/your_engineering_team_looks_healthy_it"},{"short_id":"dantuo","created_at":"2026-04-20T05:24:36.000-05:00","title":"Casilda 1.2.4 Released","url":"https://blogs.gnome.org/xjuan/2026/04/19/casilda-1-2-4-released/","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"FedericoSchonborn","user_is_author":false,"tags":["c","graphics"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dantuo","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dantuo/casilda_1_2_4_released"},{"short_id":"4p1oys","created_at":"2026-04-20T04:16:49.000-05:00","title":"Diagnosing Random MariaDB Freezes","url":"https://frappe.io/blog/frappe-cloud/diagnosing-random-mariadb-freezes-on-frappe-cloud","score":6,"flags":0,"comment_count":2,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"ankush","user_is_author":false,"tags":["databases","debugging"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/4p1oys","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/4p1oys/diagnosing_random_mariadb_freezes"},{"short_id":"30vbek","created_at":"2026-04-20T04:09:21.000-05:00","title":"bpfvet: analyzes compiled .bpf.o files and reports minimum kernel version, helpers, maps, and portability issues","url":"https://github.com/boratanrikulu/bpfvet","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eBuilt this to answer \"what's the oldest kernel this BPF program can run on?\" without reading changelogs.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFeed it any .bpf.o file and it tells you:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMinimum kernel version (computed from helpers, prog types, map types)b\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTransport mechanism (RingBuf, PerfEventArray, maps)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCO-RE coverage and BTF presence\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSuperseded helper usage (bpf_probe_read -\u0026gt; bpf_probe_read_kernel)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWorks on compiled ELF, not source-language agnostic.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Built this to answer \"what's the oldest kernel this BPF program can run on?\" without reading changelogs.\r\n\r\nFeed it any .bpf.o file and it tells you:  \r\n- Minimum kernel version (computed from helpers, prog types, map types)b \r\n- Transport mechanism (RingBuf, PerfEventArray, maps)  \r\n- CO-RE coverage and BTF presence   \r\n- Superseded helper usage (bpf_probe_read -\u003e bpf_probe_read_kernel)\r\n\r\nWorks on compiled ELF, not source-language agnostic.","submitter_user":"boratanrikulu","user_is_author":true,"tags":["linux","networking"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/30vbek","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/30vbek/bpfvet_analyzes_compiled_bpf_o_files"},{"short_id":"y5nowq","created_at":"2026-04-20T04:07:49.000-05:00","title":"Modern Frontend Complexity: essential or accidental?","url":"https://binaryigor.com/modern-frontend-complexity.html","score":11,"flags":1,"comment_count":17,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"BinaryIgor","user_is_author":true,"tags":["web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/y5nowq","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/y5nowq/modern_frontend_complexity_essential"},{"short_id":"1akblt","created_at":"2026-04-20T03:17:56.000-05:00","title":"Obelisk 0.37: JavaScript, Deployments, Cron","url":"https://obeli.sk/blog/announcing-obelisk-0-37/","score":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"tomas","user_is_author":true,"tags":["release","rust","wasm"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/1akblt","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/1akblt/obelisk_0_37_javas